	<task type="small talk">
		<turn type="student">Hi, can I have <Z corr="a conversation in English">an English conversation</Z> <FS corr="with">whit</FS> you?</turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">Absolutely! I'd be happy to have a conversation with you in English. What's on your mind?</turn>
		<turn type="student"><DMCC corr="Another">another</DMCC> question?</turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">Of course! What's your next question?</turn>
		<turn type="student"><DMCC corr="Can">can</DMCC> you ask me another question?</turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">Sure! Here’s a question for you:
		If you could travel anywhere in the world right now, where would you go and why?</turn>
		<turn type="student"><DMCC corr="My">my</DMCC> favorite city <GPP corr="\0">it</GPP>'s Barcellona, I<GVAUX corr="\0">'m</GVAUX> go <LSADV corr="there">here</LSADV> every year but, I <XVCO corr="would like to go">would like go</XVCO> <LSPR corr="to">in</LSPR> Madrid, Valencia, Vienna and my <LP corr="dream travel">travel dream</LP> <GPP corr="\0">it</GPP>'s <GVNF corr="to visit">visit</GVNF> Tokyo</turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">That sounds like a great list of places to visit! Barcelona is such a vibrant city with its architecture and culture. What do you love most about Barcelona? And what interests you about Tokyo?</turn>
		<turn type="student">About Barcelona my favorite <LSN corr="piece of architecture">architecture</LSN> are Sagrada Familia because <GPP corr="it">she</GPP>'s <GA corr="the">a</GA> biggest monument in the middle of town, and <GPP corr="I">\0</GPP> <WO corr="like very much"><LSADV corr="">very much</LSADV> like</WO> <GPP corr="\0">me</GPP> Parc Guell, Casa Batlò and Barceloneta. Tokyo interests me for <GDO corr="its">his</GDO> cooking <FS corr="culture">colture</FS></turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">Those are excellent choices! Sagrada Familia is truly a masterpiece, and Parc Güell has such a unique and colorful vibe. The food culture in Tokyo is fascinating, with everything from street food to fine dining. Are there any specific dishes or types of cuisine you’re excited to try when you visit Tokyo?</turn>
	</task>
	<task type="role play">
		<turn type="student"><DMCC corr="Now">now</DMCC>, <LP corr="do a role play">simulate role play</LP></turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">Sure! Let's do a role play. You can choose a scenario or I can suggest one. How about a travel conversation where you’re planning your trip to Tokyo, and I’m a travel agent helping you with suggestions? Would that work for you?</turn>
		<turn type="student"><CSINTER corr="Translate into Italian"><DMCC corr="Traduci">traduci</DMCC> in italiano</CSINTER></turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">Certo! Ecco la traduzione:
		"Certamente! Facciamo un gioco di ruolo. Puoi scegliere uno scenario oppure posso suggerirne uno. Che ne dici di una conversazione di viaggio in cui stai pianificando il tuo viaggio a Tokyo e io sono un agente di viaggio che ti aiuta con dei suggerimenti? Va bene per te?"</turn>
		<turn type="student"><DMCC corr="Yes">yes</DMCC></turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">Great! Let’s start the role play.
		Travel Agent: Hello! Welcome to our travel agency. I hear you're interested in planning a trip to Tokyo. What dates are you considering, and what kind of experiences are you looking for?</turn>
		<turn type="student">Hello! <DMCC corr="The">the</DMCC> <GNN corr="dates">date</GNN> is from 20 September to 5 October, <Z corr="?">I would change a food <FS corr="culture">colture</FS></Z>, in particular sushi and visit the <GNC corr="city's monuments"><GNN corr="monuments">monument</GNN> city</GNC> and <GNN corr="film">films</GNN> <GNN corr="sets">set</GNN></turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">Travel Agent: That sounds fantastic! You’ll have a great time in Tokyo during that period. For sushi, I can recommend some top sushi spots, like Tsukiji Outer Market for fresh seafood and some renowned sushi restaurants in the city.
		As for monuments and film sets, you should definitely visit the Tokyo Tower and the historic Asakusa district with the Senso-ji Temple. Are there any specific movies or shows you’re interested in that were filmed in Tokyo?</turn>
		<turn type="student">Doraemond, Inazuma Eleven and <GA corr="\0">the</GA> <CSINTRA corr="comics">Fumetti</CSINTRA></turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">Travel Agent: Great choices! For Doraemon, you can visit the Fujiko F. Fujio Museum in Kawasaki, which is not too far from Tokyo. It’s dedicated to the works of the creator of Doraemon.
		For Inazuma Eleven, while specific filming locations might be harder to find, you could check out the various football-themed attractions around the city, as football is very popular in Japan.
		As for comics (fumetti), you should definitely explore Akihabara, known as the mecca for anime and manga culture. There are many stores where you can find merchandise and enjoy the vibrant atmosphere. Would you like recommendations for any specific activities or accommodations during your stay?</turn>
		<turn type="student"><CSINTER corr="Translate the last question for me"><DMCC corr="Traducimi">traducimi</DMCC> l'ultima domanda</CSINTER></turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">Certo! Ecco la traduzione:
		"Vuoi raccomandazioni per qualche attività specifica o per sistemazioni durante il tuo soggiorno?"</turn>
		<turn type="student"><CSINTER corr="Both options, but I do you say it in English?"><DMCC corr="Entrambi">entrambi</DMCC> le informazioni, ma come si dice in inglese?</CSINTER></turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">You can say: "I would like recommendations for both specific activities and accommodations during my stay."</turn>
		<turn type="student"><DMCC corr="Ok">ok</DMCC>, I would like recommendations for both specific activities and accommodations during my stay</turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">Travel Agent: Excellent! For activities, here are a few recommendations:
		Food Tour: Join a sushi-making class or a food tour in Tsukiji Outer Market to learn more about Japanese cuisine.
		Anime and Manga Shops: Spend some time in Akihabara exploring shops dedicated to anime and manga, including Doraemon and Inazuma Eleven merchandise.
		Themed Cafés: Visit a themed café, such as a cat café or a Doraemon-themed café, for a unique dining experience.
		Cultural Experiences: Consider participating in a traditional tea ceremony or visiting a sumo practice session.
		For accommodations, I recommend:
		Shinjuku: A vibrant area with many hotels, restaurants, and easy access to public transport. Check out the Hotel Gracery Shinjuku, which features a Godzilla theme.
		Shibuya: Known for its famous crossing and youthful vibe. The Shibuya Excel Hotel Tokyu offers great views and convenience.
		Asakusa: Close to Senso-ji Temple, it has a more traditional feel. Consider staying at the Asakusa View Hotel.
		Would any of these activities or accommodations interest you?</turn>
		<turn type="student"><DMCC corr="Ok">ok</DMCC> this informations <GPP corr="\0">it</GPP>'s sufficient but<QR corr="\0">,</QR> I have a big passion, Japanese <LSN corr="Motocross bikes">Motocross</LSN> <LSPR corr="such as">as</LSPR> Yamaha,Honda and Kawasaki, when can I go to visit them?</turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">Travel Agent: That’s fantastic! If you’re passionate about Japanese motocross, you’ll definitely want to visit some of the manufacturers’ facilities and exhibitions. Here are some options:
		Yamaha: You can visit the Yamaha Communication Plaza in Iwata, which showcases Yamaha's history and products, including motocross bikes. It’s about a 2-hour train ride from Tokyo.
		Honda: The Honda Collection Hall at the Twin Ring Motegi motorsports complex has a vast collection of Honda's history, including motorcycles. It’s also about 2 hours from Tokyo by train.
		Kawasaki: The Kawasaki Good Times World museum in Kobe is dedicated to Kawasaki’s motorcycles, but it’s further away (about 3 hours by train). If you're up for the trip, it’s worth it!
		To make the most of your time, consider scheduling visits to these places on weekends when you have more time to explore. Would you like help with travel arrangements or more details on any specific location?</turn>
